[0.374355, "o", "\u001b[1G\u001b[0K⠙"]
[0.386669, "o", "\u001b[1G"]
[0.387005, "o", "\u001b[0K"]
[3.009644, "o", "\u001b[1m\r\n  AQUEDUCT — an LLM buys specific data from a big Tap (via the aqueduct skill)\r\n\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2mdataset:\u001b[0m NASA exoplanet archive (real)   \u001b[2mquestion:\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.011034, "o", "  \u001b[1mOf all known exoplanets, which 5 temperate ones — equilibrium temperature between 200 and 320 K — lie closest to Earth? Give each planet's name, its distance in parsecs, and its equilibrium temperature.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.380943, "o", "\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[36m  1  SERVE — compile the exoplanet archive into a Tap and run it\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.965356, "o", "  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[0m server wallet \u001b[2m(pre-funded)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[3.993094, "o", "  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[0m \u001b[1m1,529 planets\u001b[0m live on http://localhost:8700  \u001b[2m(0.0001 pathUSD/row)\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[36m  2  DISCOVER — the agent reads the Tap's terms for free (skill: --schema)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[6.928883, "o", "  \u001b[2mcolumns:\u001b[0m name:string  host_star:string  discovery_year:integer  method:string  distance_pc:number  period_days:number  radius_earth:number  mass_earth:number  eq_temp_k:integer\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[36m  3  PLAN — the LLM translates the question into a paid query\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[13.110705, "o", "  \u001b[2mLLM query →\u001b[0m \u001b[36m{\"select\":[\"name\",\"distance_pc\",\"eq_temp_k\"],\"filters\":[{\"field\":\"eq_temp_k\",\"op\":\"gte\",\"value\":200},{\"field\":\"eq_temp_k\",\"op\":\"lte\",\"value\":320}],\"sort\":[{\"field\":\"distance_pc\",\"dir\":\"asc\"}],\"limit\":5}\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[36m  4  BUY — the agent pays per row over an MPP session (skill: paid query)\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[13.299668, "o", "  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[0m agent wallet \u001b[2m(pre-funded)\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[19.944016, "o", "  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[0m bought \u001b[1m5 rows\u001b[0m for \u001b[1m0.0005 pathUSD\u001b[0m  \u001b[2msettled 0x04d65270e3340e3e…\u001b[0m\r\n      \u001b[2mhttps://explore.testnet.tempo.xyz/tx/0x04d65270e3340e3e6ee8b16fab61a9c68d8dc16a743af833d55de0910d0e4364\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n\u001b[1m\u001b[36m  5  ANSWER — the LLM answers from only the rows it bought\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n  \u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[30.15421, "o", "  Closest 5 temperate (200–320 K) exoplanets:\r\n\r\n| Planet | Distance (pc) | Eq. temp (K) |\r\n|---|---|---|\r\n| GJ 414 A b | 11.89 | 309 |\r\n| LHS 1140 b | 14.99 | 226 |\r\n| TOI-4336 A b | 22.55 | 309 |\r\n| TOI-2134 c | 22.62 | 306 |\r\n| LP 890-9 c | 32.43 | 272 |\r\n\r\nNotable:\r\n- **GJ 414 A b** — nearest, 11.89 pc. Warm sub-Neptune/super-Earth near upper temp edge (309 K).\r\n- **LHS 1140 b** — coldest here (226 K), well-studied rocky super-Earth orbiting nearby M dwarf, prime habitability/atmosphere target.\r\n- **LP 890-9 c** — farthest of five but 272 K sits mid-range, near liquid-water sweet spot; second planet of TOI-4306 system.\r\n- Big distance gap: two close (~12–15 pc), then jump to ~22 pc cluster. All orbit cool M dwarfs — tight orbits give these moderate temps.\r\n"]
[30.15459, "o", "\u001b[32m\u001b[1m\r\n  ✓ DONE — answered from 5 paid rows, never touching the other 1,524.\r\n\u001b[0m\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[30.200314, "o", "\u001b[1G\u001b[0K"]
[30.200502, "o", "⠙"]
